00:03:09.320 --> 00:03:10.830
learning method. And then there's a

00:03:10.840 --> 00:03:14.110
buffer of states of a fixed size.

00:03:14.120 --> 00:03:15.590
You're going to need this ring buffer

00:03:15.600 --> 00:03:16.750
for states. You're going to need a

00:03:16.760 --> 00:03:17.990
buffer for advantages and you're going

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:19.990
to need an index buffer.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:23.150
The way that the algorithm works is

00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:25.790
the first time you do rollouts

00:03:25.800 --> 00:03:27.750
or the first step, the first time step

00:03:27.760 --> 00:03:30.030
every time you do rollouts, if the

00:03:30.040 --> 00:03:32.110
warm-up buffer isn't full yet,

00:03:32.120 --> 00:03:33.790
then you're going to put all of those

00:03:33.800 --> 00:03:37.229
initial states into the buffer.

00:03:38.350 --> 00:03:38.360
Uh

00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:40.390
but once it is full, you're only going

00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:42.470
to put a certain fraction of the

00:03:42.480 --> 00:03:45.150
environment states into the buffer.

00:03:45.160 --> 00:03:46.750
And the rest of them are going to have

00:03:46.760 --> 00:03:48.630
their state set

00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:50.509
using prioritized experience replay

00:03:50.519 --> 00:03:53.750
sampling over the existing state buffer.

00:03:53.760 --> 00:03:55.230
You have a bunch of previously recorded

00:03:55.240 --> 00:03:56.830
states, you're going to sample from

00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:58.870
them, and you're going to sample ones

00:03:58.880 --> 00:04:00.990
more often that have high absolute

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:02.830
advantage estimate. So, these should be

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:05.110
high information states.

00:04:05.120 --> 00:04:06.830
During training, you compute your

00:04:06.840 --> 00:04:08.430
advantage across all the segments. This

00:04:08.440 --> 00:04:10.350
is going to be used to update the

00:04:10.360 --> 00:04:13.470
priority of the buffer.

00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:18.270
And you are going to sample segments

00:04:18.280 --> 00:04:20.870
from the the current data buffer.

00:04:20.880 --> 00:04:22.870
This is basically exactly as before. It

00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:24.470
still uses prioritized replay, but it's

00:04:24.480 --> 00:04:28.510
a different prioritized replay buffer.

